extensionName.description: Please keep in mind that these strings had to be approved by the Google Brand Features Team. Be sure to make clear that this extension is *FOR* Google Calendar and not *BY* Google. Also, it was explicitly stated, that the phrase 'Google Calendar' should be localized just as it is on the localized versions of the Google Calendar UI.

extensionDescription.message: Sireg anekcum si sin idisan ɣer uwiyitay Google

gdata.migration.description.message: Asaǧǧaw i uwitay Google yeffa-d d akken llan iwitayen ur yemiren ara ad kecmen ɣer iwitayen n Google deg uskar n tɣuri kan. Ma tebɣiḍ ad tessaliḍ aswir n yiwen seg iwitayen-agi, fren-iten daw-a.

gdata.wizard.session.description.message: Ma ulac aɣilif, fren tiɣimt neɣ sekcem tansa imayl akken ad ternuḍ tiɣimit tamaynut. Tesriḍ kan yiwet n tɣimit i yiwen n umiḍan.

gdata.wizard.calendars.description.message: Ma ulac aɣilif fren tibdarin n iwitayen akked twuriwin anda tebɣid ad tejerredeḍ.

gdata.wizard.nextstep.description.message: Ma ulac aɣilif ddu ɣer imecwar d-iteddun akken ad tesbaduḍ iwitayen-inek.

busyTitle.description: Events with only free/busy access don't have a title, they will use this title instead. The calendar name is used as a parameter, since its often named after the person whose calendar you are viewing.
